question: Georgia Contractor License Requirements
answer: Georgia requires contractors to be licensed for work over $2,500. General contractor license requires 4 years experience or equivalent education. Application fee is $200, with total costs ranging $300-400. Two exams required: Business & Law (110 questions, 4 hours) and Trade exam (110 questions, 4 hours). Both require 70% passing score. $10,000 surety bond required for general contractors. This information is time-sensitive.

question: Texas - No State Licensing Required
answer: Texas does not require state-level general contractor licensing. Must check municipal requirements for specific cities/counties. No age, experience, or educational requirements at state level. State licensing required for specific trades: Plumbing (Responsible Master Plumber), HVAC (Class A/B with insurance requirements), Electrical (2+ years journeyman before master). Municipal bonds may be required (example: San Antonio demolition $5,000 annual bond). This information is time-sensitive.

question: Washington State Simple Licensing Requirements
answer: Washington has among the simplest contractor licensing: No experience requirements, no education requirements, no examination for general contractors. $30,000 surety bond (increased July 2024), $250,000 minimum general liability insurance ($200K public liability + $50K property damage OR $250K combined). Registration fee $141.10 for 2 years. Must register with Secretary of State, obtain UBI number, get EIN. 3-4 week processing for mail applications. This information is time-sensitive.

Registration fee $141.10 for 2 years. Must register with Secretary of State, obtain UBI number, get EIN. 3-4 week processing for mail applications. This information is time-sensitive.
